      &lt;h1> PHP Indexed Arrays  &lt;h1>
      &lt;p>  There are two ways to create indexed arrays:   &lt;/p>
      &lt;p>  The index can be assigned automatically (index always starts at 0), like this:   &lt;/p>
      &lt;!--
      $cars = array("Volvo", "BMW", "Toyota");
      $cars[0] = "Volvo";
      $cars[1] = "BMW";
      $cars[2] = "Toyota";
      <!-- :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::: -->
      &lt;/body></pre>
      <!-- ------ end html -------- -->
      <hr>
